NAME: Accounting treatment
DESCRIPTION: Defines whether the item is entirely or partially recognized or derecognized in the accounting statements of the reporting institution.

NAME: Type of allowance
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the type of allowance for credit losses.

NAME: Accounting portfolio
DESCRIPTION: Accounting portfolios shall mean financial instruments aggregated by valuation rules (e.g. "Available-for-sale financial assets"). Accounting portfolios only comprise financial assets and financial liabilities.

NAME: Approach for prudential purposes
DESCRIPTION: Approach used for the calculation of capital requirements.

NAME: Base
DESCRIPTION: Defines the basic conceptual meaning of a data point. Identifies the framework in which a data point is included. For FINREP, it indicates in which group of element of the financial statement should be included the data point (e.g. assets, liabilities, equity, income, expenses). For COREP, it indicates whether the data point should be computed in the numerator (own funds) or the denominator (exposures) of the Pillar I solvency ratio. It determines whether the data point has a "debit" or a "credit" attribute.

NAME: Business line
DESCRIPTION: Defines the business line that generates operational risk.

NAME: Calculation method
DESCRIPTION: Identifies the method used to calculate values (e.g. sums)

NAME: Covered bond issuance
DESCRIPTION: For each cover bond issuance, consists of the name or unambiguous abbreviation of the covered bond issuing entity and the designation of the covered bond that individually is subject to the relevant covered bond protective measures

NAME: Country of the market
DESCRIPTION: Defined the country in which is located the market on which the instrument is traded.

NAME: Controlling and non-controlling owners
DESCRIPTION: For equity components, it indicates whether they belong to the owners of the parent or to non-controlling owners (minority interests).

NAME: Counterparty sector of the collateral
DESCRIPTION: Defines the institutional sector of the counterparty of financial instruments received/given as collateral.

NAME: Counterparty sector of the source of encumbrance
DESCRIPTION: Defines the counterparty sector of the transactions that pose a source of encumbrance

NAME: Counterparty sector
DESCRIPTION: Defines the sector of the counterparty of financial instruments (e.g. Central banks or Credit institutions).

NAME: Size of the counterparty
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the size category of the counterpart

NAME: Credit rating agency /Covered bond regime
DESCRIPTION: For each issuance of covered bonds, specifies both the credit rating that rates the issuance and the local statutory regime

NAME: Contingent scenario/Assumptions used
DESCRIPTION: Contingent scenario whose impact is reported

NAME: Currency with significant liabilities
DESCRIPTION: Defines the currencies of the significant liabilities

NAME: Derivatives Purchased/Sold
DESCRIPTION: For derivatives, it indicates whether the reporting institution has sold or purchased them.

NAME: Exposure class of the collateral received
DESCRIPTION: For Liquidity purposes, defines the exposure class of the collateral received

NAME: Encumbrance
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the condition related to the encumbrance of the asset

NAME: Time of encumbrance
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the time that the assets is expected to remain encumbered.

NAME: Exposure class
DESCRIPTION: Defines the exposure class for capital requirement purposes

NAME: Forbearance status
DESCRIPTION: Identifies the financial assets and off-balance sheet items with forbearance measures and, if applicable, the type of forbearance measures

NAME: Financial reporting standard
DESCRIPTION: Financial reporting standard for recognition, measurement and presentation (IFRS or national GAAP) to define the scope of reported items.

NAME: Fair value hierarchy
DESCRIPTION: Determines the level in the fair value hierarchy to which the estimation belongs.

NAME: Hybrid instruments
DESCRIPTION: For financial instruments, it indicates whether there are hybrid instruments (i.e. that combine a host contract with embedded derivative contracts) or not.

NAME: Impairment status
DESCRIPTION: Status for monitoring credit quality of financial assets and off-balance sheet items (e.g. past due, impaired, defaulted).

NAME: Location of the activities
DESCRIPTION: Identifies the nature of the geographical area where activities are undertaken. "Location" means the jurisdiction of incorporation of the legal entity which has recognised the asset or liability; for branches, it means the jurisdiction of residence.

NAME: Legal entity
DESCRIPTION: Defines the entity code of the entity for which information is provided.

NAME: Is LEI Code/National Code of Holding
Liquidity quality of assets
DESCRIPTION: Liquidity conditions specified for assets under the liquidity provisions framework

NAME: Liquidity quality of collateral received
DESCRIPTION: Liquidity conditions specified for collateral received under the liquidity provisions framework

NAME: Main category of hedging instrument
DESCRIPTION: Defines the main category of the instrument used for hedging.

NAME: Instrument
DESCRIPTION: Defines instrument or product type of the main category item

NAME: Main category of collateral or guarantee given
DESCRIPTION: Defines the main category of collateral or guarantees given

NAME: Main category of the Defined benefit plan assets
DESCRIPTION: For defined benefit plan assets, defines their nature.

NAME: Main category that generates income or expenses
DESCRIPTION: Defines the main category that generates the related income or expense.

NAME: Hedged or hedging instrument
DESCRIPTION: Defines hedging or hedged instrument of the main category item

NAME: Main category of collateral or guarantee received
DESCRIPTION: Defines the main category of collateral or guarantees received

NAME: Main category of hedged item
DESCRIPTION: Defines the main category of the item that is hedged.

NAME: Main category provided of Investee
DESCRIPTION: When information on an "investee-by-investee" basis is provided, specifies the main category of the information on the investee to be reported.

NAME: Main category that generates the provision
DESCRIPTION: Defines the main category that generates the related provisions.

NAME: Main category of the source of encumbrance
DESCRIPTION: For encumbered assets, defines the main category of the transaction that entails encumbrance; for liabilities/contingent liabilities, identifies those who are a source of encumbrance

NAME: Main category of the transferred financial asset to which the liability is associated to
DESCRIPTION: For liabilities associated to transferred financial assets, defines the type of instrument of the financial asset that has been transferred.

NAME: Main category of the underlying
DESCRIPTION: Defines the type of instrument underlying another balance or transaction (e.g. short position).

NAME: Main category
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the nature of the item reported (i.e. answers the question: what is reported?). For financial instruments, defines the instrument (e.g. deposits, debt securities issued...) or range of instruments reported. It should be defined for each data point.

NAME: Current period (flow)
DESCRIPTION: Current period (flow)

NAME: Fair value
DESCRIPTION: Fair value

NAME: Present value
DESCRIPTION: Present value

NAME: NACE code counterparty
DESCRIPTION: Defines the NACE code of the counterparty, whenever it is applicable.

NAME: Observation_Value
DESCRIPTION: Observation_Value

NAME: Own funds
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the eligibility for the various levels of own funds for the fully phased-in period (without transitional provisions).

NAME: Date / period of application of forbearance measure
Performing status
DESCRIPTION: Identifies the performing status of financial assets and off-balance sheet items (performing, non-performing...)

NAME: Designation (Fair value option)
DESCRIPTION: Defines the reason for designating an instrument to the portfolio for financial instruments designated at fair value through profit or loss (use of fair value option).

NAME: Accounting portfolio of the transferred financial asset to which the liability is associated to
DESCRIPTION: For liabilities associated to a transferred financial asset, it defines the accounting portfolio of the transferred financial asset.

NAME: Prudential portfolio
DESCRIPTION: Defines whether it is reported the trading book business, the "banking" book business, or both of them.

NAME: Purpose
DESCRIPTION: Defines the purpose of a balance or transaction.

NAME: Residence of counterparty
DESCRIPTION: Defines the geographical area where the counterparty of the contract or transaction resides.

NAME: To be reclassified to profit or loss
DESCRIPTION: For the accumulated other comprehensive income items, it indicates whether they could be reclassified to profit and loss.

NAME: Reference date or period
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the date or the period to which the data is referred

NAME: Residual maturity
DESCRIPTION: Time remaining from the reporting date to the maturity date.

NAME: Related parties/Relationships
DESCRIPTION: Defines the relationship between the reporting institution with an entity or a person; in particular, it specifies the type of related party.

NAME: Reported Period
DESCRIPTION: Reported period

NAME: Riad Code
DESCRIPTION: Riad Code

NAME: Specific contract clauses or netting agreements
DESCRIPTION: Defines specific contract clauses or netting agreements.

NAME: Scope of consolidation
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the scope of consolidation of reporting when different from CRR scope

NAME: Subject to operating lease (reporting entity lessor)
DESCRIPTION: For tangible and intangible assets, it indicates whether they are subject to operating leases in which the reporting institution is the lessor.

NAME: Securitisation structure
DESCRIPTION: Defines the tranche of the exposure in the securitisation structure.

NAME: Security
DESCRIPTION: When information is provided on a security-by-security basis, defines the code of the security for which information is provided.

NAME: Subordinated
DESCRIPTION: Indicates that the financial instrument is a subordinated financial asset or liability.

NAME: Transfer between impairment stages
DESCRIPTION: Defines transfers of debt instruments subject to impairment between the impairment stages.

NAME: Time past due
DESCRIPTION: For debt instruments that are past due, time passed between the date on which the payment was due and the reference date.

NAME: Type of risk
DESCRIPTION: Indicates the type of risk arising from exposures or transactions (e.g. credit risk or market risk).

NAME: Type of risk transfer
DESCRIPTION: Defines the way in which a risk has been transferred in a securitisation (traditional or synthetic securitisations).

NAME: Type of activity
DESCRIPTION: Defines the type of activity (e.g. asset management or custody).

NAME: Is LEI Code/National Code of Investee
Type of hedge
DESCRIPTION: Defines the type of hedging

NAME: Type of activity of Related parties/Relationships
DESCRIPTION: Defines the nature of the activities of related parties.

DESCRIPTION: Unit
